==EDGE瀕危物種==

在2008年1月21日，进化特殊的{{le|全球濒危物種組織|EDGE of Existence programme}}（簡稱EDGE）找出了自然界中“最離奇”、“最美妙”和“最瀕危”的物種，並指出：“EDGE的[[兩棲動物|兩棲動物]]是地球上最值得注意和最獨特的物種，可是前100名中有85%的物種正遭受棲息地減少或無棲息地的境況。” 其中，幽靈蛙在EDGE中被列入前10名。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.reuters.com/article/latestCrisis/idUSL2038808 |title=Reuters, Giant newt, tiny frog identified as most at risk |accessdate=2011-07-12 |archive-date=2009-02-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090220211707/http://www.reuters.com/article/latestCrisis/idUSL2038808 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/environment/2008/jan/21/conservation |title=guardian.co.uk, Drive to save weird and endangered amphibians |accessdate=2011-07-12 |archive-date=2010-08-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100821022924/http://www.guardian.co.uk/environment/2008/jan/21/conservation |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/environment/gallery/2008/jan/21/wildlife.conservation |title=guardian.co.uk/environment, Gallery: the world's strangest amphibians |accessdate=2011-07-12 |archive-date=2012-04-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120416224744/http://www.guardian.co.uk/environment/gallery/2008/jan/21/wildlife.conservation |dead-url=no }}</ref>

